The Ponale is a  long river originating in Lake Ledro (Lago di Ledro).
The river first passes Molina di Ledro, Pr&lt;U+00E8&gt; di Ledro and Biacesa, there feeding a fish farm. Starting from Biacesa the Ponale enters a steep canyon and after a cascade the Ponale flows into Lake Garda close to Porto del Ponale.
